        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1085219581" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12720829713513704561">Revised rating upward: I just downloaded <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/46787.Uncle_Tom_s_Cabin' title='Uncle Tom&apos;s Cabin by Harriet Beecher Stowe' rel='nofollow noopener'>Uncle Tom&apos;s Cabin</a> and several books by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/18943.Frederick_Douglass' title='Frederick Douglass' rel='nofollow noopener'>Frederick Douglass</a> and I ordered <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/132913.Reconstruction_America_s_Unfinished_Revolution_1863_1877' title='Reconstruction America&apos;s Unfinished Revolution 1863-1877 by Eric Foner' rel='nofollow noopener'>Reconstruction: America&apos;s Unfinished Revolution 1863-1877</a>, all of which means that Candle in the Darkness had more of an impact on me than I first thought. So...bumping the rating up to 4 Stars.<br/><br/>A very readable, clean romance ideal for Christian teens or possibly younger audiences. Good introduction to the Civil War and life in the South, including thoughtful portrayals of slave life.A</span>
  <span id="freeText12720829713513704561" style="display:none">Revised rating upward: I just downloaded <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/46787.Uncle_Tom_s_Cabin" title="Uncle Tom's Cabin by Harriet Beecher Stowe" rel="nofollow noopener">Uncle Tom's Cabin</a> and several books by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/18943.Frederick_Douglass" title="Frederick Douglass" rel="nofollow noopener">Frederick Douglass</a> and I ordered <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/132913.Reconstruction_America_s_Unfinished_Revolution_1863_1877" title="Reconstruction America's Unfinished Revolution 1863-1877 by Eric Foner" rel="nofollow noopener">Reconstruction: America's Unfinished Revolution 1863-1877</a>, all of which means that Candle in the Darkness had more of an impact on me than I first thought. So...bumping the rating up to 4 Stars.<br /><br />A very readable, clean romance ideal for Christian teens or possibly younger audiences. Good introduction to the Civil War and life in the South, including thoughtful portrayals of slave life.As my new priority reads demonstrate, it's got me thinking and looking to do more serious reading about slavery, the Civil War, and the Reconstruction.<br /><br />On the downside, I found the plot a bit improbable, the characters somewhat flat and there were some dangling loose threads left at the end, but it still kept me turning the pages. <br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
