  <span id="freeText6059872224409784357" style="display:none">I read Candle in the Darkness over a year ago yet vividly remember how it touched my heart. I immediately passed it on to my sister-in-law who asked if I had a good book for her to read. The main character, Caroline, raised in the South to believe slavery was a basic part of life is challenged in her long held belief. This may be one of the best stories of that time period revealing the depth of deception people had towards ownership of slaves. I don't want to spoil the book for you. I would encourage to read Candle in the Darkness. You will be moved!<br /><br /></span>
